2026-03-18  Phase 1 start  Version 0.15.0

Goal
- Begin the migration where Rust is the application runtime and Lua is the extension/customization layer.

Changes made
- Bumped workspace version from 0.14.7 to 0.15.0.
- Updated product metadata to describe Lite-Anvil as a Rust application with Lua extensions.
- Added `forge-core/src/runtime.rs` as the Rust-owned startup/bootstrap layer for the Lua runtime.
- Moved the following startup responsibilities out of `data/core/start.lua` and into Rust:
  - AppImage working-directory restore
  - `DATADIR` resolution
  - `USERDIR` resolution
  - `PATHSEP`, `SCALE`, `VERSION`, `MOD_VERSION_*`, `EXEFILE`, `EXEDIR`, `PLATFORM`, `ARCH`
  - Lua `package.path` and `package.cpath`
  - native-plugin searcher registration
  - relative `require()` support
  - `core.utf8string` and `core.process` preload
- Changed `forge-core/src/main.rs` and `forge-core/src/lua_vm.rs` so Rust now tracks restart cycles and prepares Lua directly instead of executing `data/core/start.lua`.

Files changed
- `Cargo.toml`
- `changelog.md`
- `forge-core/Cargo.toml`
- `forge-core/src/main.rs`
- `forge-core/src/lua_vm.rs`
- `forge-core/src/runtime.rs`

Validation
- `cargo test` passed: 44 tests.
- `cargo build` passed.
- Launch smoke passed with `env SDL_VIDEODRIVER=dummy timeout 5s cargo run --quiet`.
  - Exit code `124` was expected from `timeout`.
  - No startup error output was produced during the timed run.

Issue encountered and fixed
- First launch failed because `MOD_VERSION_STRING` and related globals were previously provided by `data/core/start.lua`.
- Restored `MOD_VERSION_MAJOR`, `MOD_VERSION_MINOR`, `MOD_VERSION_PATCH`, and `MOD_VERSION_STRING` from Rust bootstrap.

Behavioral boundary after this phase
- Rust now owns the startup environment.
- Lua still owns the editor shell and built-in feature composition after bootstrap.
- `data/core/start.lua` remains in the tree as a legacy reference, but the runtime no longer depends on it for launch.

Rollback notes
- To revert only this migration slice, restore:
  - `Cargo.toml`
  - `changelog.md`
  - `forge-core/Cargo.toml`
  - `forge-core/src/main.rs`
  - `forge-core/src/lua_vm.rs`
- Remove:
  - `forge-core/src/runtime.rs`
- Expected rollback effect:
  - Launch returns to the previous Rust -> `start.lua` -> `core.init()` bootstrap path.

