- Ratio after this batch: Rust `16699`, Lua `24709`, about `40.3% Rust`.
- Remaining blocker to a truthful "finished" claim: 18 built-in plugin wrappers under `data/plugins/*.lua` still load `.luac` sidecars, and large product UIs like autocomplete/terminal/workspace/treeview remain Lua-owned above the Rust backends.
2026-03-18 parity-native-cutover:
- Switched bundled language discovery to `core.syntax` asset registration, so built-in `language_*.lua` wrappers are no longer required for bundled languages.
- Deleted all bundled language wrappers except `language_md.lua`, which remains only for Markdown-specific styling behavior.
- Removed all stale built-in `.luac` sidecars under `data/core`, `data/plugins`, and `data/colors`; built-in sidecar count is now `0`.
