2026-03-19 native-extraction-pass: statusview + treeview + builtin-preload decomposition

Goal
- Move actual Rust logic into the two largest built-in preloads (`statusview`, `treeview`) by
  extracting pure state/model code from embedded Lua SOURCE bodies into proper Rust functions.
- Decompose the monolithic `builtin_embeds.rs` into per-module native files so each built-in
  owns its own preload registration.

Changes made

builtin_embeds.rs decomposition
- Added `node_native.rs`, `rootview_native.rs`, `doc_module_native.rs`, `docview_native.rs`,
  `commands_doc_native.rs` — each a thin shim (~18 lines) that registers its builtin as a
  package preload.
- Wired each shim via `mod.rs`; removed the corresponding `insert_preload` calls from
  `builtin_embeds.rs`.
- `builtin_embeds.rs` now registers only `core_runtime`. Everything else is owned by its
  respective native file.
- Removed `builtins/core_statusview.rs` and `builtins/plugins_treeview.rs` (dead after the
  native files took ownership).

statusview_native.rs (new)
- Replaced the 1165-line embedded SOURCE with a 601-line BOOTSTRAP thin wrapper + 524 lines
  of Rust native functions.
- Rust now owns: `init`, `normalize_position`, `get_item`, `remove_item`, `move_item`,
  `order_items`, `get_items_list`, `show_message`, `apply_panel_layout`, `drag_panel`,
  `get_hovered_panel`, `get_item_visible_area`, `on_mouse_pressed`, `on_mouse_moved`,
  `on_mouse_released`.
- Net reduction: 564 fewer embedded Lua lines (1165 → 601 in the BOOTSTRAP).

treeview_native.rs (new)
- Replaced the 1126-line embedded SOURCE with a 949-line BOOTSTRAP + 370 lines of Rust.
- Rust now owns: `init` (reads config/session, sets all state fields), `sync_model` (builds
  roots/opts/project_roots from live Lua globals, calls tree_model.sync_roots, updates view
  state — absorbs the old Lua `tree_roots()` and `tree_model_opts()` helpers), `get_item_by_row`
  (range-cache + item_at lookup, reads model_roots/project_roots from self), `get_items_in_range`
  (range-cache + bulk lookup), `set_selection` (selection state + scroll computation),
  `update_hover` (hover/tooltip state from mouse coordinates), `apply_scale_metrics` (sets all
  font-metric fields and resets label caches — absorbs the old `on_scale_change` body).
- Lua BOOTSTRAP collapsed functions: `new()` 14→3 lines, `sync_model()` 15→5 lines,
  `on_scale_change()` 21→6 lines, `on_mouse_moved()` 39→23 lines.
- Net reduction: 177 fewer embedded Lua lines (1126 → 949 in the BOOTSTRAP).

